<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-06T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.0055/1</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-06T17:00:00+00:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7:40 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Diplomatic corps convened for this evening to discuss subject of my
                            August 5, 9 a.m. Care of Americans requires my constant attention. The
                                <hi rend="italic">Tennessee</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d105fn1">Warship
                                bringing gold for the relief of American citizens.</note> is about
                            to arrive at Ostend, therefore I feel that I can render more real
                            service by remaining here. I should like Department’s views.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>